s very important to both of us. He's in the back there.



 Today, here at the White House, 10 individuals from across the country w=
ill be honored as White House Champions of Change. They've been selected =
from over 900 nominations for their leadership in preventing prescription=
 drug abuse and heroin use, and for increasing access to treatment and to=
 support their fellow Americans in recovery -- for supporting their fello=
w Americans in recovery.=20



 This is a disease that can touch anybody, and all of us can help reduce =
drug abuse through evidence-based treatment, prevention, and recovery. Re=
search shows it works. And courageous Americans show it works every day. =
I'm so nervous I can't believe. (Laughter.) So thank you for the opportun=
ity to be here today, and to highlight this important issue. And now I re=
